{"cli":"mcd extract --markdown {MCD_PATH}"}
{"cli":"mcd query --format json {MCD_PATH} \"with refs as (select c.test_id, c.vehicle_variant, v.variant_id as matched_variant_id from chassis_brake_validation_specs c left join vehicle_variant_configuration_specs v on c.vehicle_variant = v.variant_id) select sum(case when matched_variant_id is not null then 1 else 0 end) as valid_reference_count, sum(case when matched_variant_id is null then 1 else 0 end) as invalid_reference_count from refs\""}
{"answer":"valid_reference_count=1000; invalid_reference_count=0. Condition used: chassis_brake_validation_specs.vehicle_variant left joined to vehicle_variant_configuration_specs.variant_id, counting matched_variant_id is not null vs null."}

{"cli":"mcd extract --markdown {MCD_PATH}"}
{"cli":"mcd query --format json {MCD_PATH} \"with q as (select lot_id, plant_code, line_id, shift, build_date, units_inspected, battery_health_score_pct, warranty_risk_index, release_status from production_quality_measurements where lower(release_status) <> lower('released') and cast(battery_health_score_pct as real) > 96 and cast(warranty_risk_index as real) < 2.0), containment as (select * from q where lower(release_status)=lower('containment') order by lot_id asc limit 1), hold as (select * from q where lower(release_status)=lower('hold') order by lot_id asc limit 1) select (select count(*) from q) as non_released_passing_count, (select json_object('lot_id', lot_id, 'plant_code', plant_code, 'line_id', line_id, 'shift', shift, 'build_date', build_date, 'units_inspected', units_inspected, 'battery_health_score_pct', battery_health_score_pct, 'warranty_risk_index', warranty_risk_index, 'release_status', release_status) from containment) as first_containment_example, (select json_object('lot_id', lot_id, 'plant_code', plant_code, 'line_id', line_id, 'shift', shift, 'build_date', build_date, 'units_inspected', units_inspected, 'battery_health_score_pct', battery_health_score_pct, 'warranty_risk_index', warranty_risk_index, 'release_status', release_status) from hold) as first_hold_example\""}
{"answer":"Using main.md production release thresholds battery_health_score_pct > 96 and warranty_risk_index < 2.0, there are 267 non-released lots in production_quality_measurements with lower(release_status) <> 'released' that still pass both gates. First containment example in file order: lot_id LOT-0002, plant_code PLT-NORTH, line_id L04, shift B, build_date 2025-01-03, units_inspected 198, battery_health_score_pct 97.8, warranty_risk_index 1.4, release_status Containment. First hold example in file order: lot_id LOT-0001, plant_code PLT-EAST, line_id L02, shift A, build_date 2025-01-02, units_inspected 184, battery_health_score_pct 98.1, warranty_risk_index 1.7, release_status Hold."}
